cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.Distributed, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with shared memory algorithms in a distributed system, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses solutions to fundamental problems such as mutual exclusion and consensus, which are related to data structures and algorithms.
3. cs.Distributed - The paper deals with a fully anonymous model in a distributed system, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The concept of anonymity is related to security and privacy, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with a system of processes accessing shared memory, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
